  Source:
    Title: Harijan
    Editor: Mohandas Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 28 Oct 1937
---
Restraint never ruins one's health. What ruins one's health is not restraint
but outward suppression. A really self-restrained person grows every day
from strength top strength and from peace to more peace. The very first
step in self-restraint is the restraint of thoughts.
